text: Yesterday craving for satay saw the stall closed no more satay, BBQ chicken and otak, saw the coffee shop owner cleaning the stall and he told me no manpower to work, (Taman Jurong 101 coffee shop)

They don’t deserve 1 star. See yourself please. My satay (take away) at the counter there and she don’t even call me. I just sitting infront of her. Waste time waste money. Her face so black, I don’t knw what I’ve done or she doesn’t like her job.

‼️WORST SERVICE EVER‼️
❌DO NOT RECOMMEND❌
lady talked as if talking to ants ( wearing mask some more ) , double checked price and still couldnt hear her , then guy beside her shouted the amount to me , wanted to double confirm again as was getting takeout and wasnt sure if they charge for plastic , and she raised her voice at me and rolled her eyes at me too
if u wanna talk SO softly in such a noisy environment , dont expect ur customers to be able to hear u
boyf went back to collect food and she spoke VERY rudely to him as if he owe her like bro ur customers dont owe u anyt .
dont have work attitude then dont work in service line .
Definitely deserves the 1.5 stars… horrible service especially the front lady with horrible attitude and also have horrible food quality. Avoid at all COST! DO NOT RECOMMEND!
Worth the wait for the satay. The pork satay is delicious  charred and the peanut sauce is nice and not spicy cheers
